article.description: Makai Mason scored 16 points and Yale defeated 59-50 on Friday night to remain a half-game ahead of Princeton in the Ivy League race.
article.headline: Yale sweeps Harvard 59-50 to remain on top of Ivy League
article.linkText: Yale sweeps Harvard 59-50 to remain on top of Ivy League
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Makai Mason scored 16 points and Yale defeated 59-50 on Friday night to remain a half-game ahead of Princeton in the Ivy League race. Justin Sears had 12 points and Brandon Sherrod 11 for the Bulldogs (19-6, 10-1), who swept the Crimson for the first time since 2008. That was also the last time the Crimson (11-16, 3-7), who won the last five Ivy League championships, finished with a losing record. Harvard was 11-18, 5-11 in 2007-08, coach Tommy Amaker's first season. Nick Victor had 11 rebounds to go with nine points and Sears had nine rebounds, plus five assists, as the Bulldogs had a 37-29 rebounding advantage. Yale broke away from a 5-5 tie with a 10-0 run and was up 36-22 at the half. Harvard scored the last 10 points of the game. Patrick Steeves had 16 points and Agunwa Okolie 11 for the Crimson.
